	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Foreseeing the problems with getting the original MS-DOS versions of SnowBro's Tile Layer and NSA to work on a machine running NT (that is, win2k/winxp/vista), I wrote my own clones of the programs, called 8TED and 8name respectively. See <a href="http://www.pineight.com/pc/#ted" class="postlink">Pin Eight NES Tools</a>. In 8TED, if you try to open a nonexistent file, it will create a new file of 8192 bytes, and then you can press Ctrl+R to resize it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


